OL,3,CRachel Reeves insists welfare reforms
OL,4,Cwill 'lift people out of poverty'
OL,6,FThe government's own impact assessment
OL,7,Fhas estimated that 250,000 more
OL,8,Fpeople, including 50,000 children,
OL,9,Fwill be left in relative poverty after
OL,10,Fhousing costs by the end of the decade.
OL,12,FThe decision to tighten eligibility
OL,13,Ffor Pip will impact 800,000 disabled
OL,14,Fpeople who will lose an average of
OL,15,F#4,500 a year.
OL,17,FThat figure includes 370,000 current
OL,18,Frecipients and 430,000 future Pip
OL,19,Frecipients.
